# Keep the Docker build context small AND ensure host-built (macOS) artifacts
# never leak into the linux images. Everything below is regenerated inside the
# image by `pnpm install` / `nest build` / `next build`.
**/node_modules
**/.next
**/dist
**/.turbo
.git
**/*.tsbuildinfo

# Local env + editor/OS cruft. ALL dotenv variants are excluded (runtime env
# comes from compose, never baked into the image) — next build would otherwise
# read a stray gitignored .env.production and inline its NEXT_PUBLIC_* values.
**/.env*
!**/.env.example
.DS_Store
**/.DS_Store

# Docs / non-build assets.
**/*.md
*.pdf

# Repo areas that never belong in the api/web images (the ai-stack runs as its
# own compose project; docs/tasks/.claude are not build inputs).
ai-stack/
docs/
tasks/
.claude/
.github/
